Mokelumne River Instream Flow to Habitat Area Relationship

A dataset containing the Weighted Usable Area (WUA) in square feet per 1000 feet as a function of flow in cubic feet per second

mokelumne_river_instream

Format

dataframe with 14 rows and 5 variables:

flow_cfs

integer flow value in cubic feet per second

FR_spawn_wua

spawning WUA in square feet per 1000 feet

FR_fry_wua

fry (up to 50 mm) WUA in square feet per 1000 feet

FR_juv_wua

juvenile WUA in square feet per 1000 feet

watershed

name of watershed

Source

EBMUD 2016 and CDFW 1998

Details

The spawning WUA values were derived from the EBMUD 2016 SRH2D model and the rearing from the CDFW 1998 PHABSIM.
